{"type":"message","id":"a9b58e83","parentId":"e892ae28","timestamp":"2026-03-30T01:26:53.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the output, I can see:\n1. Monitor connected: HDMI-1 (2560x1440)\n2. There's a `/dev/dri/card1` which is likely the discrete GPU (RTX 2070)\n3. No nvidia-smi installed, so NVIDIA driver might not be loaded\n4. There's a render node `renderD128` which could be either GPU\n\nThe fact that there's only 1 monitor on HDMI-1 and the RTX 2070 has HDMI output, it's likely connected to the 2070. But since there's no nvidia-smi, the NVIDIA driver might not be loaded or even installed.\n\nLet me check which GPU is actually rendering.\n","thinkingSignature":"f380a7bd3f9b0963ebeea82c3d3ec64f3aa6e3ed1631a287e650673181094ad5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l83h02xj78b0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 设备信息 ===\" && lspci | grep -E \"VGA|Display\" && echo -e \"\\n=== Xorg日志中的GPU使用 ===\" && (grep -i \"using\\|connected\\|output\" /var/log/Xorg.0.log 2>/dev/null | tail -20 || journalctl -b --no-pager | grep -i gpu 2>/dev/null | tail -10) && echo -e \"\\n=== 活跃GPU驱动 ===\" && ls -la /sys/class/drm/ 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"card[0-9]|HDMI|DP\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":343,"output":307,"cacheRead":16384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17034,"cost":{"input":0.0001029,"output":0.0003684,"cacheRead":0.00049152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00096282}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774834007382,"responseId":"06190457c59c818f33254fde9b65b47f"}}
